  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. A mesh-independence verification activity (MRL5-MESH-VERIF) is declared via hasVerificationActivity and described in prose throughout the assessment, but no evidence artifact carries a prov:wasGeneratedBy reference back to that activity IRI — creating an activity-evidence consistency gap (W-CON-05).",
