      "name": "Hemolysis index benchmark comparison against FDA experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index values were compared against FDA in-vitro experimental measurements for the generic centrifugal pump at five operating points. The mesh-independence study (MRL5-MESH-VERIF) established that numerical discretization error is controlled; however, the model systematically over-predicts hemolysis by 18–34% across operating points. Uncertainty bounds from Monte Carlo sampling do not encompass all experimental values. Validation fails the absolute threshold criterion at MRL 5.",
