      "description": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed with 500 samples propagating uncertainty in blood viscosity, pump rotational speed tolerance, and inlet flow boundary conditions. The 95th-percentile hemolysis index prediction exceeds the clinical threshold at two of five operating points. The numerical convergence behaviour documented in the mesh study (MRL5-MESH-VERIF) was cited in the narrative but the evidence artifact here was produced by the UQ execution activity, not the mesh verification activity.",
