      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic comparison of all QoIs against experimental data with statistical metrics and uncertainty overlap analysis.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index comparisons were performed at all five operating points. Mean absolute relative error of 26.4% exceeds acceptable tolerance. Uncertainty intervals do not overlap experimental values at two operating points. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs must directly correspond to clinical decision metrics; hemolysis index must be mapped to clinical threshold.",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis index is directly mapped to the clinical threshold. However, sub-lethal hemolysis markers and platelet activation are not captured. Achieved level 3 vs required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, blood analogue, and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experiments used a glycerol-water blood analogue rather than porcine blood. Pump geometry is the generic FDA model, not a patient-specific VAD. Relevance gap is significant at MRL 5. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
