      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty must be characterised through sensitivity analysis across alternative turbulence and hemolysis constitutive models.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was used without comparison to alternative turbulence closures. The Giersiepen hemolysis power-law was adopted without sensitivity to alternative damage accumulation models. Model form uncertainty is large and unquantified. Achieved level 2 vs required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
